      <reaction compartment="compartment_17941" fast="false" id="reaction_170850" metaid="metaid_103" name="Phosphorylated SMAD2/3 dissociates from TGFBR" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Upon phosphorylation of the R-SMAD (SMAD2/3), the conformation of the C-terminal (MH2) domain of the R-SMAD changes, lowering its affinity for the type I receptor and ZFYVE9 (SARA). As a result, the phosphorylated R-SMAD dissociates from the activated receptor complex (TGFBR).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
