      <reaction compartment="compartment_876" fast="false" id="reaction_2127562" metaid="metaid_105" name="STRAP binds phosphorylated TGF-beta receptor complex" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">STRAP (serine-threonine kinase receptor-associated protein) binds to the activated TGF-beta receptor complex. In in vitro studies, STRAP is able to bind both TGFBR1 and TGFBR2 (Datta et al. 1998). This was deduced from experiments in which a recombinant mouse Strap and recombinant human TGFBR1 and TGFBR2 were expressed in COS1 cells. STRAP is also able to bind unphosphorylated TGF-beta receptor complex, but the physiological significance, if any, of this interaction is not known.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
