      <reaction compartment="compartment_171062" fast="false" id="reaction_170868" metaid="metaid_116" name="Activated type I receptor phosphorylates SMAD2/3 directly" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Activated type I receptor kinase directly phosphorylates two of the C-terminal serine residues of SMAD1, SMAD5 or SMAD8. Binding of these R-SMADs to the L45 loop of the type I receptor is critical for this event.</p>
        </notes>
