      <reaction compartment="compartment_7660" fast="false" id="reaction_178215" metaid="metaid_123" name="SMAD7:SMURF1 complex is exported to the cytosol" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">After SMAD7:SMURF1 complex binds to XPO1 (CRM1) through the nuclear export signal (NES) in the C-terminus of SMURF1, XPO1 enables transport of SMAD7:SMURF1 to the cytosol (Suzuki et al. 2002, Tajima et al. 2003). A recombinant mouse Smad7 and recombinant human SMURF1 were used in these experiments.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
