      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_4332236" metaid="metaid_137" name="CBL neddylates TGFBR2" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">CBL neddylates TGFBR2 on lysine residues K556 and K567. The E3 ubiquitin ligase activity of CBL is necessary for this modification, and the kinase activity of TGFBR2 is also required. CBL-mediated neddylation prolongs the half-life of TGFBR2, thereby enhancing signaling by the TGF-beta receptor complex. CBLB, a CBL-related protein, may cooperate with CBL in TGFBR2 neddylation (Zuo et al. 2013).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
